A bit of an odd duck, this instrument once again uses Tim Escobedo's Ghost Dance Wah circuit (https://nexp.pt/escobedo.html), based around the 4069 hex inverter chip. There are touch points on the audio input and the resonance potentiometer, and the output is run through a homemade Electro-Harmonix LPB-1 boost pedal (https://beavisaudio.com/schematics/Electro-Harmonix-LPB-1-Schematic.htm). The sound ends up coming through an overdriven PAM8403-based amplifier, which produces odd clicks and hums when the touch points are tapped and the resonance knob is twisted. This instrument is a "Qollision" between a Quacker and a Screecher because of these two methods of interaction.
